Former Crime Intelligence boss, Richard Mdluli was convicted of assault and kidnapping related to the 1998 disappearance of his alleged lover. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Too old and vulnerable for jail, at least, that's what former Crime Intelligence boss, Richard Mdluli is claiming in the High Court in Johannesburg during his sentencing proceedings. Mdluli was convicted of assault and kidnapping related to the 1998 disappearance of his alleged lover. READ: Hawks official details how Mdluli investigations stalled He is asking the court to impose a sentence of correctional and community service.